│ Now, apply the more complete fix.                                                          │
│                                                                                            │
│ <tool_call>                                                                                │
│ {                                                                                          │
│   "name": "edit",                                                                          │
│   "args": {                                                                                │
│     "file": "llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp",                             │
│     "old": "      if (E->isSame(VL)) {\n        // Record the reuse of the tree node.\n    │
│ E->UserTreeIndices.push_back(UserTreeIdx);\n        LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << \"SLP: Perfect    │
│ diamond merge at \" << *S.getMainOp()\n                          << \".\\n\");\n           │
│ return;\n      }",                                                                         │
│     "new": "      if (E->isSame(VL)) {\n        // Record the reuse of the tree node.\n    │
│ E->UserTreeIndices.push_back(UserTreeIdx);\n        // If the entry was created as a       │
│ gather, it may not have operations\n        // set. Now that we are reusing it as a        │
│ vectorizable entry, set them.\n        if (!E->hasState()) {\n                             │
│ E->setOperations(S);\n          E->State = TreeEntry::Vectorize;\n        }\n              │
│ LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << \"SLP: Perfect diamond merge at \" << *S.getMainOp()\n                │
│ << \".\\n\");\n        return;\n      }"                                                   │
│   }                                                                                        │
│ }                                                                                          │
│ </tool_call>                                                                               │
│ This seems much more robust. It ensures that when a `TreeEntry` is reused, it is fully     │
│ updated to reflect its new role as a vectorizable node, not just partially initialized. I  │
│ will now verify this.                                                                      │
